# ORDER BY CLAUSE :
-- Order by clause is used to arrange the records in ascending or descending order.
-- It executes at the last after the execution of select clause.
-- Executes group by group.
-- Column used in group by cluase should be used in order by clause.
-- It is the only clause which executes after the select.

# SYNTAX :
          SELECT */ [DISTINCT] COLUMN_NAME/ EXPRESSION [ALIAS]
          FROM TABLE_NAME
          ORDER BY COLUMN_NAME ASC/DESC;

          SELECT MRF_FUNCTION/ GROUP_BY_EXPRESSION
          FROM TABLE_NAME
          [WHERE <FILTER_CONDITION>]
          [GROUP BY COLUMNS]
          [HAVING <GROUP_FILTER_CONDITION>]
          ORDER BY GROUP_BY_COL_EXPR;
-- Effect of group by clause

# EXECUTION PRINCIPLE
1. FROM     - Fetch table from db.
2. WHERE    - row by row
3. GROUP BY - row by row
4. HAVING   - group by group
5. SELECT   - group by group
6. ORDER BY - row by row.

1. WAQTD sal in ascending order.
